        <<face "Friend" 1>>
        Rirma: It will just have to be some other time.
        <<face "Friend" 2>>
        Rirma: But my father is growing old, so he's probably just going to give me more work to do here at the store.
        Rirma: No, I guess it won't ever happen.
        Rirma: Time goes on and we will grow old and bitter. 
        Rirma: Then, one by one, we're going to die off.
        Rirma: In the end, the last one of us will sit alone and wish that we could just spend one more day together.
        <<face "Friend" 1>>
        Nohkan: Okay! I'm comming along!
        Nohkan: Could you just... stop saying such things?
        Rirma: I knew I could count on you!
        Nohkan: ...
        Nohkan: What are we even going to do?
        Rirma: Don't worry about that, I have something planned.
        Nohkan: That makes me worry more.
        Rirma: It's going to be fun!
        Rirma: Now, hurry on home. Go to bed early so that you will be sharp and ready tomorrow.
        Nohkan: (What have I gotten myself into?)
